content.description:
Interesting moves all the way. If only this were longer. 

  Maneuver up under right side of roof. Exit Right, next up left a little, up right a little to an easy handhold. Then one last move up left, and top out. 

  . . (First Ascent: the 2011 guidebook and the Rakkup phone app say that the roof had been sent, but above to the top was still a "project". Jared finished the project).
content.protection:
Top-Rope: Could set top anchor with long slings or short static line from tree above. 

  Protection for Trad leading is unknown and likely inadequate.
content.location:
The obvious big cave near the left end of this wall.

content.description:
Fun crux sequence, but too short. 

  Up to the roof, then up through 5-inch crack in its left side.
content.protection: Trad: Forget the standard rack, bring the big guns.Top-Rope could be done from anchor off tree above.
